al Cursor hook implementation, I can see the difference between the two scenarios the user described. In session 1, when Cursor makes the commit directly while the session is still active, the prepare-commit-msg hook fires and finds an ACTIVE session, adding the trailer through the agent communication mechanism. But in session 2, the user commits manually after Cursor exits, which means SessionEnd fires first, then the user's manual commit triggers prepare-commit-msg with the trailer already in place, allowing the post-commit condense to work properly.\\n\\nThe critical issue is that when Cursor commits mid-turn while ACTIVE, SaveStep hasn't fired yet since that only happens on TurnEnd, so the shadow branch might not have the current session's data. The code sets `sessionHasNewContent` to true for ACTIVE sessions, but `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck` relies on checking what files were touched before, which could be missing or stale if the shadow branch hasn't been updated with the latest turn data. Even with the fix, there's still an issue in scenario 1 where the agent commits mid-session: the transcript path gets set correctly during `InitializeSession`, but then when `post-commit` fires and tries to extract files from the live transcript, I need to verify whether `CursorAgent` actually implements the `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":34404,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":109201,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":34404},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYWzbahp1t63EhWpoEnTp\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"2ffa128c-5a60-42cc-bea8-13ae55d7f085\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T16:27:10.958Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2ffa128c-5a60-42cc-bea8-13ae55d7f085\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/